The paper discusses signal processing tasks and their relationship with reproducing kernel Hilbert spaces, which is a common topic in the sub-category of cs.SP (Signal Processing). The paper also introduces a new framework for kernel-based learning, which is a popular topic in the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also discusses sparse linear regression, nuclear-norm regularization, and dictionary learning, which are all topics in the sub-category of cs.IT (Information Theory). The paper also provides examples of applications in cognitive radio sensing, microarray data imputation, and network traffic prediction, which are all topics in the sub-category of cs.NA (Numerical Analysis). Finally, the paper discusses the impact of sparse KBL on signal processing applications, which is a topic in the sub-category of cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
